I'll help you create a comprehensive design system prompt and a reference navigation file for your black & white Web3 project. Here's what you need:

## **Master Design System Prompt**

```
DESIGN SYSTEM SPECIFICATION - BLACK & WHITE WEB3 PROJECT

CORE PRINCIPLES:
- Strictly black (#000000) and white (#ffffff) color scheme
- Sharp, geometric borders (border-radius: 0px always)
- Space Mono font family for all text
- Minimalist, brutalist aesthetic
- Web3/crypto-native feel

TYPOGRAPHY:
- Primary font: 'Space Mono', monospace
- Font weights: 400 (regular), 700 (bold)
- Heading hierarchy: text-4xl, text-3xl, text-2xl, text-xl
- Body text: text-base, text-sm
- All text either black or white for maximum contrast

BUTTON PATTERNS:
- Default: bg-black text-white border-2 border-black hover:bg-white hover:text-black
- Secondary: bg-white text-black border-2 border-black hover:bg-black hover:text-white
- Disabled: bg-gray-200 text-gray-400 border-2 border-gray-200
- Sizes: px-6 py-3 (default), px-4 py-2 (small), px-8 py-4 (large)
- Always use transition-all duration-200 for hover effects

FORM ELEMENTS:
- Inputs: bg-white border-2 border-black focus:outline-none focus:border-black
- Labels: text-black font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider
- Error states: border-red-500 with red text
- Placeholders: text-gray-500

LAYOUT PATTERNS:
- Containers: max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4
- Grid systems: grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
- Spacing: space-y-4, space-y-6, space-y-8 for vertical rhythm
- Borders: always 2px solid, never rounded

COMPONENT STYLING:
- Cards: bg-white border-2 border-black p-6
- Navigation: bg-black text-white with white hover states
- Modals: bg-white border-4 border-black with black backdrop
- Tables: border-collapse with alternating black/white rows

INTERACTIVE STATES:
- Hover: Invert colors (black becomes white, white becomes black)
- Active: Add slight scale transform: scale-95
- Focus: Thick black outline, no rounded corners
- Loading: Black/white pulsing animation

ICONOGRAPHY:
- Use simple, geometric icons
- Always black or white, no colors
- Sharp edges, no rounded icon styles
- Consistent stroke width

RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR:
- Mobile-first approach
- Stack vertically on small screens
- Maintain sharp edges across all breakpoints
- Text remains readable at all sizes
```

## **Reference Navigation Component**

Create this file as `src/components/ReferenceNav.jsx`:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const ReferenceNav = () => {
  const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useState('buttons');

  const sections = {
    buttons: {
      title: 'BUTTON PATTERNS',
      content: (
        
          {/* Primary Button */}
          
            Primary Action
          
          
          {/* Secondary Button */}
          
            Secondary Action
          
          
          {/* Small Button */}
          
            Small Button
          
          
          {/* Large Button */}
          
            Large Button
          
        
      )
    },
    forms: {
      title: 'FORM ELEMENTS',
      content: (
        
          
            
              Input Label
            
            
          
          
          
            
              Select Dropdown
            
            
              Option 1
              Option 2
            
          
          
          
            
              Textarea
            
            
          
        
      )
    },
    cards: {
      title: 'CARD PATTERNS',
      content: (
        
          {/* Basic Card */}
          
            CARD TITLE
            Card content goes here. This is the standard card pattern.
            
              Action
            
          
          
          {/* Inverted Card */}
          
            INVERTED CARD
            This is the inverted version of the card pattern.
            
              Action
            
          
        
      )
    },
    typography: {
      title: 'TYPOGRAPHY SCALE',
      content: (
        
          H1 HEADING
          H2 HEADING
          H3 HEADING
          H4 HEADING
          Regular body text paragraph. This shows the standard text size and spacing.
          Small text for captions and secondary information.
          BOLD UPPERCASE TEXT
        
      )
    }
  };

  return (
    
      {/* Navigation Header */}
      
        
          
            
              DESIGN SYSTEM
            
            
              {Object.entries(sections).map(([key, section]) => (
                 setActiveSection(key)}
                  className={`px-4 py-2 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider border-l-2 border-white transition-all duration-200 ${
                    activeSection === key 
                      ? 'bg-white text-black' 
                      : 'bg-black text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-black'
                  }`}
                >
                  {key}
                
              ))}
            
          
        
      

      {/* Content Area */}
      
        
          
            {sections[activeSection].title}
          
          {sections[activeSection].content}
        
      
    
  );
};

export default ReferenceNav;
```

## **Implementation Instructions**

1. **Add this to your main CSS file** (update your existing one):

```css
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap');

@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

.geist-mono {
  font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
}

/* Custom scrollbar styles */
.custom-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
}

.custom-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
  background: transparent;
}

.custom-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  border-radius: 0px;
}

.custom-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
}

@layer utilities {
  .no-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;
  }

  .no-scrollbar {
    -ms-overflow-style: none;
    scrollbar-width: none;
  }

  input[type='number']::-webkit-outer-spin-button,
  input[type='number']::-webkit-inner-spin-button {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    margin: 0;
  }

  input[type='number'] {
    -moz-appearance: textfield;
    appearance: textfield;
  }
}

/* Force sharp edges globally */
* {
  border-radius: 0 !important;
}
```

2. **Use this prompt when asking AI to build components**:

```
Build a [COMPONENT NAME] using the black & white design system. Requirements:
- Use only black (#000000) and white (#ffffff) colors
- All borders must be 2px solid with border-radius: 0
- Use Space Mono font family with geist-mono class
- Buttons: bg-black text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-black pattern
- Sharp geometric design, no rounded corners anywhere
- Include proper hover states with color inversion
- Use uppercase text with tracking-wider for labels
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Add transition-all duration-200 for smooth interactions
```

This gives you a complete reference system that you can always point back to when building new components or pages!